tant of today\u2019s culture and social systems, but many people are unaware of how easily simple passwords are cracked. I could explain some of the dangers myself, but instead let me reference this and this other xkcd, which touch on two of the most important points. But then I would also reference this video which goes a few steps further- it goes on to not only explain, but demonstrate some of the methods used in cracking passwords. It\u2019s quite scary, in my opinion, watching it crack thousands in the space of a few seconds. (The same channel also has some other good videos on the topic.) The takeaways being to use a password manager, don\u2019t have short passwords and use a password manager because that\u2019s the way to do it.Continuing with a personal recommendation, I\u2019ve found LastPass to be a good password manager. It\u2019s rated higher than its competitors, has more features generally speaking, and I haven\u2019t had any issues with it so far. I would implore each of you to look into the topic.", "link_list": ["https://xkcd.com/936/", "https://xkcd.com/792/", "https://youtu.be/7U-RbOKanYs", "https://www.lastpass.com/"], "image_list": [], "html": "<i>Improve your password security.</i>"}, "post-70439": {"user": "Leviath Bahat", "user_num": 122, "timestamp": "1499707067000", "message": "Jul 10, 2017 5:30:21 GMT -8 Empress Naoki said:Improve your password security.Passwords are a massively important of today\u2019s culture and social systems, but many people are unaware of how easily simple passwords are cracked. I could explain some of the dangers myself, but instead let me reference this and this other xkcd, which touch on two of the most important points. But then I would also reference this video which goes a few steps further- it goes on to not only explain, but demonstrate some of the methods used in cracking passwords. It\u2019s quite scary, in my opinion, watching it crack thousands in the space of a few seconds. (The same channel also has some other good videos on the topic.) The takeaways being to use a password manager, don\u2019t have short passwords and use a password manager because that\u2019s the way to do it.Continuing with a personal recommendation, I\u2019ve found LastPass to be a good password manager. It\u2019s rated higher than its competitors, has more features generally speaking, and I haven\u2019t had any issues with it so far. I would implore each of you to look into the topic.I would like to add to remember all the security links on your accounts. Is your main email linked to another email for security purposes that you forgot about and has a weak password? Where possible, use security links that are difficult to exploit - such as your phone number for text messages; but always have more than one. I lost access to an account last year because I had an authentication app on my phone and then broke my phone. A good idea is to have your mobile phone and your house phone as security back-ups and if the service offers you some sort of un-redeemable recovery code that you can use to get temporary, one-time access back into your account, then write it down somewhere safe and don't lose it.Make sure never to store passwords in plain text files on your PC. Also remember that memorising passwords is always a better alternative than leaving any kind of trace, whether electronic or physical.", "link_list": ["/post/70437/thread", "/user/607", "https://xkcd.com/936/", "https://xkcd.com/792/", "https://youtu.be/7U-RbOKanYs", "https://www.lastpass.com/"], "image_list": ["https://i.imgur.com/jxxfhPa.jpg"], "html": "<div author=\"@madamenaoki\" class=\"quote\" source=\"/post/70437/thread\" timestamp=\"1499693421\"><div class=\"quote_body\"><div class=\"quote_avatar_container\"><div class=\"avatar-wrapper avatar_size_quote avatar-607\" title=\"Empress Naoki\"><img alt=\"Empress Naoki Avatar\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/jxxfhPa.jpg\"/></div></div><div class=\"quote_header\"><a href=\"/post/70437/thread\">